The paper presents a novel continuous-time probabilistic model for risk prognosis of deteriorating patients in regular wards, which involves learning from clinical judgments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
